  }, {
    "href": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epiphany_(feeling)"
  }), "epiphany"), ". He had been investigating vibrating strings, and found that when you cut the length of the string in half, the note it makes is an octave higher."), mdx("p", null, "Sound is vibration. When one sound is vibrating twice as fast as another, it still sounds the same in some crucial way. The pitch is higher, or lower, but somehow we perceive it as having the same essential character. A C note, multiplied or divided by two as many times as you like, still sounds like a C."), mdx("p", null, "Here are all eight C\u2019s on the piano. They are different in pitch, but all have the same character. ", mdx("a", _extends({
