    allowFullScreen: true
  }), mdx("p", null, "Pythagoras\u2019 epiphany still has merit. Cosmologists have imagined many alternate universes, with different basic physical constants and laws, curved space, more dimensions \u2014 but it\u2019s pretty tough to imagine a universe without number. I believe the integers \u2014 1, 2, 3 and so on, are the most basic things we know about for sure."), mdx("p", null, "Pythagoras actually founded a ", mdx("a", _extends({
