    "id": "notes-and-intervals"
  }, "Notes and Intervals"), mdx("p", null, "A note, in music, is a sound with a particular pitch. Pitch is frequency, measured in cycles per second, or Hertz (Hz). The faster the vibration, the higher the pitch."), mdx("p", null, "A vibration, at, say, 220 Hz, all by itself is a note by that general definition. But the note doesn\u2019t acquire its distinct personality until it\u2019s considered in relation to some other note. That relationship is called an interval."), mdx("p", null, "Here is that 220 Hz note, played on a cello, all by itself: ", mdx("a", _extends({
