  }), "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ve-u_spRpgk")), mdx("p", null, "The final note is an octave plus a major second above the tonic \u2014 a major ninth. Its ratio is (3/2) x (3/2), or 9/4. It has a haunting sound, to me, a different beauty certainly. A new crayon in the box."), mdx("h2", {
    "id": "the-major-seventh"
  }, "The Major Seventh"), mdx("p", null, "The notes get more exotic as you move outward from the center. The ninth is quite consonant, but not nearly as consonant as the fifth. (", mdx("a", _extends({
